Package: DICi
Title: Parameterization-Invariant Deviance Information Criterion for Latent Variable Models
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Xingyao", "Xiao", email = "xingyao.xiao@stanford.edu",
           role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Sophia", "Rabe-Hesketh", email = "sophiarh@berkeley.edu",
           role = "aut")
  )
Description: Computes DIC_i, a parameterization-invariant, plug-in-free
    version of the Deviance Information Criterion for Bayesian model
    comparison (Xiao and Rabe-Hesketh, 2026, <arXiv:2605.27844>). DIC_i adds
    the variance-based penalty of Gelman, Hwang and Vehtari (2014,
    <doi:10.1007/s11222-013-9416-2>) to the posterior mean deviance instead
    of the plug-in deviance used by the classical DIC. By removing the
    plug-in deviance, DIC_i is invariant to reparameterization and therefore
    robust to the multimodal posteriors caused by sign switching, label
    switching, and parameterization switching in latent variable models.
    DIC_i is asymptotically equivalent to WAIC but does not require pointwise
    likelihood factorization.
